cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a new method for classification on tabular data using two-dimensional embeddings and fine-tuned two-dimensional CNN models. This approach combines techniques from computer vision (two-dimensional embeddings and CNN models) and natural language processing (word embeddings) to address a problem in structured data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, since the paper proposes a novel approach to address a specific problem, it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
